From: Tony Ascendr <upstream-author>
Date: ambassador branch baseline
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] Add AmbassadorModule + NodeDB + Modules.cpp registration

Adds the AmbassadorModule that DMs newly-discovered nodes with the first
configured canned message. This patch is upstream from
https://github.com/ascendr/firmware/tree/ambassador and is included here
verbatim so EFMesh customizations (patches 0002, 0003) apply cleanly.

The AmbassadorModule source files (src/modules/AmbassadorModule.cpp and
src/modules/AmbassadorModule.h) are checked in directly under
src/modules/ in this repo. Drop them into a clean Meshtastic firmware
checkout at the same path.

Wire-up edits required in upstream files:

--- a/src/modules/Modules.cpp
+++ b/src/modules/Modules.cpp
@@ -27,6 +27,7 @@
 #include "modules/AdminModule.h"
+#include "modules/AmbassadorModule.h"
 #include "modules/CannedMessageModule.h"
@@ -137,6 +138,7 @@
 #if !MESHTASTIC_EXCLUDE_NODEINFO
     nodeInfoModule = new NodeInfoModule();
+    ambassadorModule = new AmbassadorModule();
 #endif

--- a/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp
+++ b/src/mesh/NodeDB.cpp
@@ -23,6 +23,7 @@
 #include "main.h"
+#include "modules/AmbassadorModule.h"
 #include "mesh/wifi/WiFiAPClient.h"
@@ -1915,6 +1916,9 @@
